data.title: Beaconsfield NOW!
data.meta_description: The Beaconsfield Society is a local amenity group that celebrates the past, promotes the present and influences the future in Beaconsfield, UK.
data.text:
JFK: The Last Speech event - June 2019

Special film screening celebrating Robert Frost, Americaâ€™s premier poet and one-time resident of Beaconsfield, with a talk by Director Neil Bicknell

Nick Park film night - May 2019

A Grand Film Night Out at the NFTS, celebrating 30 years of Nick Park's Wallace & Gromit

Alison Uttley plaque unveiling - December 2018

Installation of a plaque to celebrate Alison Uttley, children's author and Beaconsfield resident

Sir Terry Pratchett week - October 2018

A week of events to celebrate 70 years since the birth of best-selling author and Beaconsfield resident Sir Terry Pratchett

NFTS visit - July 2018

Heritage visit to the National Film and Television School in Beaconsfield

Alison Uttley celebration - July 2017

A celebration of the life and work of Alison Uttley, children's author and Beaconsfield resident, including children's activities and a talk by her biographer Professor Denis Judd
